		"description": "{html}<div><p>When trying to spin an imageView with controlled degrees on each\r\ncall without any duration in the animation, the image resets to\r\n0deg before the transform is applied with the animate. More\r\ndescription and example found here:<br>\r\n<a href=\r\n\"http://developer.appcelerator.com/question/32961/continuous-rotation\">\r\nhttp://developer.appcelerator.com/question/32961/continuous-rotation</a>\r\nand here<br>\r\n<a href=\r\n\"http://developer.appcelerator.com/question/10181/multiple-rotates-of-view-with-animation-part-2\">\r\nhttp://developer.appcelerator.com/question/10181/multiple-rotates-o...</a></p>\r\n<p>A possible solution would be to be able to apply the transform\r\ndirectly on the UI object without having to call animate when you\r\njust want it to instantly move without taking the time to do an\r\nanimation.</p></div>{html}",
		"attachment": [],
		"flagged": false,
		"summary": "iOS: Rotate transform animate flickers to rotate 0 with each turn",
